STUDY TITLE
------------
A Phase II, Randomised, Double-Blind, Placebo-Controlled Study to
Evaluate the Efficacy and Safety of DEM-042 in Participants with
Advanced Non-Small Cell Lung Cancer (synthetic study).

OBJECTIVES
-----------
  Primary:   Objective response rate (ORR) per RECIST v1.1
  Secondary: Progression-free survival (PFS)
             Duration of response (DOR)
             Overall survival (OS)
             Safety and tolerability

STUDY DESIGN
--------------
  • Randomisation: 2:1 (DEM-042 : placebo)
  • Stratification: ECOG PS (0 vs 1), prior lines of therapy (1 vs ≥2)
  • Blinding: Double-blind (participants, investigators, sponsor)
  • Treatment Duration: Until progression or unacceptable toxicity

STUDY POPULATION
------------------
  Target Enrollment: 400 participants (synthetic)
  Key Inclusion:
    1. Age ≥ 18 years
    2. Histologically confirmed NSCLC (Stage IIIB/IV)
    3. ≥ 1 prior line of systemic therapy
    4. ECOG Performance Status 0–1
    5. Measurable disease per RECIST v1.1

  Key Exclusion:
    1. Prior treatment with selective kinase inhibitors
    2. Active CNS metastases (treated and stable ≥ 4 weeks allowed)
    3. Significant cardiovascular disease
    4. Known hypersensitivity to study drug excipients

DOSING
-------
  • DEM-042: 200 mg orally, once daily, continuous dosing
  • Dose modifications: Per protocol-specified toxicity management

