  │ Biomarker samples       │ Baseline, Week 8, at progression  │
  └────────────────────────┴────────────────────────────────────┘

STATISTICAL CONSIDERATIONS
-----------------------------
  • Primary analysis: ORR with exact binomial 95% CI
  • Sample size: 80% power to detect ORR improvement from 15% to 30%
  • Interim analysis: Planned at 50% of events (futility only)
  • Alpha: 0.05 (two-sided), adjusted for interim look

DATA MONITORING
-----------------
  • Independent Data Safety Monitoring Board (DSMB)
  • DSMB reviews: Q6M or after every 50 participants enrolled
  • Stopping rules: Predefined futility and safety boundaries

